description.author: Thomas Lippincott
description.synopsis: Library for the Concrete data format.
description.description: Concrete is a Thrift-based data specification designed for Natural Language Processing (NLP) applications.  This library provides a Haskell interface to code generated from the latest release of Concrete (the concrete-haskell-autogen package). It also has an ingest utility for converting various formats (JSON, CSV, XML, etc) to Concrete Communication objects.
